\b\fs54 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.\
Cut tops off 2 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 garlic}} heads. Wrap in foil and roast for 30 minutes. When cool enough to handle remove the flesh from the garlic heads and set aside.\
In a large stockpot, cook potatoes in enough salted water to cover for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.\
Drain and return to stockpot. Beat with an electric {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 mixer}} until smooth; adding salt, to taste, pepper, butter, garlic and sour cream. With a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/spatula/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 spatula}} stir in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 cheese}} and bacon. Add more salt and pepper, if necessary. Serve immediately.\
